prj:TechnicalJustification.prj:justificationText:
- For sensitivity;
In this science goal, we assigned 22 sample galaxies with source fluxes larger than 0.35 mJy and adopted 0.07 mJy as a required sensitivity to detect S/N>5.

- Imaging;
Our purpose of this observation is obtaining not maps but total fluxes of the sources.

- Correlator setup;
The central frequencies of 4 spectral windows of band 7 are setted to 336.5, 338.5, 348.5, 350.5 GHz with total bandwidths of 2 GHz and spectral resolutions of 31.25 MHz.
We set 0.0 as redshifts of all samples to fix the observing frequency.

- Calibration;
Default.

- Bandpass accuracy;
Default.

- Scheduling/time constraints;
No constraint.

- Data rate;
Normal.

- Special constraints on standard observing modes;
No constraint.

